The paper proposes a new method for the actor-critic contextual bandit for mobile health intervention. This involves decision-making methods in mHealth, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the issue of outliers, which is related to computational engineering, finance, and statistics (cs.CE, cs.CR, cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.LG and cs.AI, followed by cs.CE, cs.CR, and cs.SI.
